<h1>From Brigadier General William Heath</h1>

<div class="docbody">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">May it please your Excellency</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">Camp at Cambridge<br/>Febry 22nd 1776</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>I some Time Since Reported, that Colonels Prescott &amp; Phinny, had Chosen the Revd Mr Foster for the Chaplin of those Regiments<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0254-fn-0001" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0254-fn-0001-ptr">1</a> This Choice is but Temporary as it is at Present Uncertain whether Mr Foster Can be absent from his Own Parrish for more than a month or Two, I now beg leave further to report that Colonels Greaton &amp; Baldwin have made Choice of the Revd Mr Barnum for the Chaplin of their Regiments<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0254-fn-0002" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0254-fn-0002-ptr">2</a>Having Five Regiments in the Brigade under my Command, Colol Sargent finds it difficult to Joyn another Regiment, at present And as there are Nine Regiments in the Camp at Roxbury, One of them must of necessity Joyn with Some Regiment in this Camp and as the Situation of Colo. Prescotts Regt Seems to Point out that as the most Proper one it has been Proposd that Such a Junction take place, and that Colo. Sargent &amp; Colo. Phinny should Joyn, This However Seems at present a little embarrassed on Account of the uncertainty of Mr Fosters Continueing the whole Campaign. All which is Humbly Submitted By your Excellencys most Humble Servt</p>
<div class="closer">
<p class="signed">W. Heath Brigr Genl</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0254-sn">

   <p>
<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Autograph Letter Signed: a letter in the handwriting of, and signed by, the author ]">ALS</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>.
</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0254-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0254-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0219" class="document">Heath to GW, 13 Feb. 1776</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0254-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0254-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>Caleb Barnum (17371776), a Congregational clergyman from Taunton, Mass., served during 1775 as chaplain of Col. Timothy Walkers regiment at Roxbury. In the spring of this year Barnum accompanied Greatons and Baldwins regiments to New York and then went to Canada apparently with Greatons regiment which was ordered there on 15 April. Barnum was discharged
<span class="pb" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-03-03-02-pb-0353">[353]</span>
at Ticonderoga in July 1776 after becoming ill with bilious fever, and he died a short time later at Pittsfield, Massachusetts.</p>

</div>
